[
    {
        "content": "<p>My current understanding is that the need for <code>expect-fx</code> isn't / won't be needed anymore after the introduction purity inference / <code>!</code>. Are we at a point now where that can be removed from the language?</p>",
        "id": 482887597,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1731870117
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We'd probably want to be solid on the replacement's design within <code>expect</code></p>",
        "id": 482888103,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1731870520
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The last thing I saw from Richard was something like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">get</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">set</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">get</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">as</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">F</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">set</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">123</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">stored</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">get</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">123</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">F</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">stuff</span><span class=\"err\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">456</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 482888272,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1731870688
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So if an effectful function is passed to expect, we provide it get! and set! to emulate effectfulness with</p>",
        "id": 482888388,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1731870787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It may be fine to remove <code>expect-fx</code> before this is ironed out, though, as it's never been used/working</p>",
        "id": 482888492,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1731870853
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm asking because it's causing some (minor) problems with parsing &amp; formatting invariants that I'm now running into with fuzzing</p>",
        "id": 482888944,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1731871281
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't expect much of the plumbing for it would be useful with whatever new design we go with, so I'd agree with just removing it</p>",
        "id": 482889083,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1731871414
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In particular, the parser currently has to disallow keywords followed by a dash, and ends up treating them as identifiers instead. I have yet to find any useful code that this affects, but the simplest code that parses and runs into problems is: <code>try-1</code>.  That parses as the identifier try, - 1, and then formats to <code>try - 1</code> which the parser recognizes as being the keyword try.</p>",
        "id": 482889097,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1731871425
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Formatting isn't supposed to affect the syntax tree (modulo normalizations), and this violates that invariant</p>",
        "id": 482889207,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1731871520
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No bueno</p>",
        "id": 482889612,
        "sender_full_name": "Sam Mohr",
        "timestamp": 1731871893
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I think we don't need <code>expect-fx</code> anymore!</p>",
        "id": 482890595,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1731872811
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because of purity inference</p>",
        "id": 482890605,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1731872819
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/pull/7227\">https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/pull/7227</a></p>",
        "id": 482927029,
        "sender_full_name": "Joshua Warner",
        "timestamp": 1731903986
    }
]